<div dir="ltr">+1<div>great stuff</div></div><div class="gmail_extra"><br><div class="gmail_quote">2015-02-04 5:55 GMT-07:00 Jeff Squyres (jsquyres) <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:jsquyres@cisco.com" target="_blank">jsquyres@cisco.com</a>&gt;</span>:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex">OMPI devs --<br>
<br>
Per lots of previous discussions, you all know that you can&#39;t assign labels, milestones, or users to issues/pull requests on the ompi-release repo.<br>
<br>
Gilles has written a Github bot that will allow you to do these things by inserting special tokens in the text of issues/pull requests/comments.  Here&#39;s an example:<br>
<br>
   This PR fixes problem XYZ.<br>
<br>
   label:bug<br>
   label:enhancement<br>
   milestone:v1.8.5<br>
   assign:@jsquyres<br>
<br>
*** PLEASE GO TRY IT on the sandbox ompi-release-bot repo.<br>
<br>
Here&#39;s a fuller explanation of what OMPIBot does, and links to where you can try it out:<br>
<br>
    <a href="https://github.com/open-mpi/ompi-release-bot/wiki" target="_blank">https://github.com/open-mpi/ompi-release-bot/wiki</a><br>
<br>
Once we get enough people to try it/fix any bugs/etc., we&#39;ll deploy it on the ompi-release repo.<br>
